<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-57-0650 </DOCNO><TEXT>Starting from Boltzmann's equation, a method is developed for calculatingtemperature and density profiles and heat flux in a neutral gas in thepresence of a temperature gradient and an external force. A generalizedbarometric law is obtained. The influence of different cross-sectionmodels is also investigated.</TEXT></DOC>